
Netdot 0.8 Notes:

This version contains significant schema changes from version 0.7.12

#######################################################################
          - BEFORE YOU CONTINUE WITH THE INSTALLATION - 
#######################################################################

* Back up your existing database and put it in a safe place.

        # mysqldump -c netdot > /home/dir/netdot-bak.sql

* Rename the database with the following name:
        
	# cd /var/lib/mysql (or wherever your mysql database directory resides)
	# mv netdot netdot-0712

* Run the upgrade process to move your data from the old db to the new db:

        # make upgrade

* Follow the instructions in the INSTALL file to install the package.

* If things go really bad, you can always reinstall netdot-0.7.12 
  and put back your old database in place:

        # Re-install netdot-0.7.12
        # make dropdb
        # mysqladmin create netdot
        # mysqldump -c netdot-bak.sql | mysql netdot
        # mysqladmin drop netdot-0712
